        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "fix(daemon): recover systemctl user bus env for gateway commands",
        "body": "## Summary\n- derive missing Linux XDG_RUNTIME_DIR and DBUS_SESSION_BUS_ADDRESS for systemctl --user spawns used by gateway status/install\n- preserve the intended user scope when synthesizing env so sudo/root wrappers do not accidentally operate on the wrong account\n- add regressions for #63561 and the prior #64020 Codex review concern\n\nFixes #63561.\n\nCredit: thanks @mssteuer for the detailed #63561 reproduction, and thanks @MoerAI for the source PR https://github.com/openclaw/openclaw/pull/64020 that identified the missing systemctl spawn env path. This replacement carries the useful approach forward while addressing the target-user-scope review blocker.\n\nSecurity scope: #52293 is routed to central security handling and is intentionally excluded from this fix.\n\n## Validation\n- pnpm -s vitest run src/daemon/systemd.test.ts src/daemon/systemd-unavailable.test.ts src/commands/gateway-status.test.ts\n- pnpm check:changed\n\nProjectClownfish replacement details:\n- Cluster: ghcrawl-156597-autonomous-smoke\n- Source PRs: https://github.com/openclaw/openclaw/pull/64020\n- Credit: Credit @mssteuer for the #63561 reproduction where systemctl --user works in the shell but OpenClaw reports user systemd unavailable.; Credit @MoerAI and source PR https://github.com/openclaw/openclaw/pull/64020 for the prior env-derivation approach.; Address Codex review on #64020 by preserving the intended target user scope instead of deriving DBus env solely from process.getuid().; #52293 remains security-routed and should not be used as this non-security replacement path.\n- Validation: pnpm -s vitest run src/daemon/systemd.test.ts src/daemon/systemd-unavailable.test.ts src/commands/gateway-status.test.ts; pnpm check:changed\n",
